- "RTT" stands for Round Trip Time, which measures the time it takes for a signal to travel from the sender to the receiver and back;
- "Download throughput" measures the speed at which data is received from the network;
- "Upload throughput" measures the speed at which data is sent to the network;
- "Node" refers to a point in the network where data is collected;
- "Region" is a geographical area where the network nodes are located;
- "Top 5" refers to the highest ranks in the respective categories of RTT, download throughput, and upload throughput.

sql:
SELECT AVG(download_throughput) AS average_download_throughput
FROM network_performance
WHERE year = 2012;

